WEBVTT

01:47.566 --> 01:51.070
<i>In Orkney, it's said
that people who have drowned</i>

01:51.070 --> 01:52.488
<i>turn into seals.</i>

01:55.032 --> 01:56.617
<i>We call them selkies.</i>

02:12.716 --> 02:13.843
<i>At the highest tides,</i>

02:13.843 --> 02:16.637
<i>they slip off their seal skins
for the night</i>

02:16.637 --> 02:19.557
<i>and they come to the shore
as beautiful people.</i>

02:21.308 --> 02:22.935
<i>And they dance together.</i>

02:22.935 --> 02:25.646
<i>Naked in the moonlight.</i>

02:41.370 --> 02:44.373
<i>The selkies
return to the sea at dawn.</i>

02:44.373 --> 02:46.709
<i>Unless they're seen by a person.</i>

02:47.209 --> 02:49.795
<i>And then they're trapped
in their human body</i>

02:50.421 --> 02:51.505
<i>and cannot return.</i>

02:58.846 --> 03:02.099
<i>And they'll always remain
discontent on land</i>

03:02.099 --> 03:04.768
<i>because they belong to the sea.</i>

03:16.739 --> 03:17.948
Oh, everyone's gone?

03:17.948 --> 03:20.451
Yeah, everyone's gone.
More for me.

03:22.745 --> 03:25.080
Rona?
What are you doing?

03:28.417 --> 03:29.960
Please, please, please, come on.

03:29.960 --> 03:31.545
Come on, I gotta get you out.

03:32.922 --> 03:34.173
- Time to go home.
- Why?

03:35.549 --> 03:37.134
I remember...

03:37.134 --> 03:39.303
That everyone
is really long gone.

03:41.055 --> 03:42.389
No, there was, erm...

03:45.476 --> 03:47.144
The lights are on.
The lights.

03:47.144 --> 03:49.021
That really means
the night is truly...

03:49.021 --> 03:49.939
Ow...

03:49.939 --> 03:51.440
Come on,
what are you doing, Rona?

03:53.150 --> 03:54.985
We gotta get you out now,
come on.

03:54.985 --> 03:56.904
- Come on. Come on, Rona.
- Let's dance.

03:56.904 --> 03:58.948
Fine, I'll dance
with you instead.

03:59.823 --> 04:01.617
- Mm...
- Dave?

04:06.121 --> 04:07.206
Ah-ha!

04:07.206 --> 04:08.332
-Come on.
- Dave.

04:08.332 --> 04:09.750
- Give me a twirl.
-She's long gone.

04:09.750 --> 04:13.045
Come on, love. The door's there
and you're going out of it.

04:13.545 --> 04:15.464
Under the table. Out you come.

04:15.464 --> 04:16.799
Come on. Out you come.

04:16.799 --> 04:18.300
- You're leaving now.
- You can't see me.

04:18.300 --> 04:20.427
- Right, right, right, Dave.
- Come on. Up you go.

04:20.427 --> 04:22.554
Stand up. Stand up.

04:22.554 --> 04:24.390
To the door.

04:25.182 --> 04:26.600
You're nearly there. Come on.

04:27.643 --> 04:28.936
You've had a bit too much.

04:28.936 --> 04:30.437
Dave,
please just get her out.

04:30.437 --> 04:32.564
- God, I'm strong.
-Come on.

04:32.564 --> 04:34.191
- Come on.
- Dave, what are you gonna do?

04:34.191 --> 04:35.693
You gonna make me leave?

04:35.693 --> 04:38.070
- I'm gonna take you outside.
-Rona!

04:38.070 --> 04:38.988
You're gonna

04:38.988 --> 04:40.614
- fucking make me leave?
- Enough!

04:41.073 --> 04:42.950
Fucking arsehole! Ahh!

04:44.368 --> 04:46.328
-Time to go.
- Get off of me!

04:47.246 --> 04:48.497
Ow!

04:48.497 --> 04:50.332
- Make him stop!
- Time to go.

04:51.792 --> 04:53.002
Arsehole!

05:11.603 --> 05:13.397
Hey, you need a ride?

05:14.106 --> 05:15.858
I can give you a lift,
if you like.

05:26.201 --> 05:27.369
Rona.

05:27.369 --> 05:29.830
Um, is it okay if I get
some details from you?

05:29.830 --> 05:31.040
- Mm-hmm.
- Yeah?

05:31.040 --> 05:32.541
Just check your age.

05:33.125 --> 05:34.126
Twenty-nine.

05:34.668 --> 05:35.669
And...

05:36.336 --> 05:37.713
What's your occupation?

05:39.256 --> 05:41.425
Er, I'm unemployed right now.

05:42.551 --> 05:44.511
But I got a masters in biology.

05:48.474 --> 05:49.850
Just get a few more details.

05:52.519 --> 05:55.064
So, are there any illnesses
that run in the family?

05:55.064 --> 05:57.524
Anything, like any heart attacks
or strokes?

05:57.524 --> 05:58.609
No.

05:59.568 --> 06:00.903
Any diabetes?

06:00.903 --> 06:01.987
No.

06:02.529 --> 06:05.324
Anyone in the family
have any kind of mental illness?

07:42.004 --> 07:43.005
Come on.

07:54.016 --> 07:55.684
- I'll just leave it here.
- Thanks.

08:21.210 --> 08:22.377
How's Dad?

08:23.462 --> 08:24.463
He's fine.

08:24.463 --> 08:27.216
I heard he's been putting
his rants on Facebook again?

08:28.050 --> 08:29.051
He's not.

08:31.428 --> 08:32.638
Have you decided what color

08:32.638 --> 08:34.348
you're gonna
paint the walls yet?

08:34.848 --> 08:36.141
What do you think?

08:37.267 --> 08:38.435
I found...

08:40.145 --> 08:42.814
There's a sort of a... duck egg?

08:43.732 --> 08:45.067
- Not sure.
- That's nice.

08:45.067 --> 08:46.235
Yeah.

08:46.235 --> 08:48.528
That'd be nice
in the living room, I think.

08:50.239 --> 08:52.616
Matches your trousers.

08:58.413 --> 08:59.414
Oh.

09:00.707 --> 09:02.209
Look what I found.

09:02.209 --> 09:03.961
The RSPB is hiring.

09:03.961 --> 09:05.379
For summer jobs.
They're looking for--

09:05.379 --> 09:07.631
I have a life
that I have to get back to.

09:09.216 --> 09:11.260
I know, of course.
And I'll pray for you.

09:11.260 --> 09:12.970
Mum. Don't do that.

09:12.970 --> 09:14.805
Of course I do.

09:18.892 --> 09:20.519
Rona, do you want some tea?

09:20.519 --> 09:21.937
I'll be down in a bit.

09:22.980 --> 09:23.981
Okay.

09:32.948 --> 09:35.951
I'm really bored.

09:38.078 --> 09:40.706
Are you bored too?

09:40.706 --> 09:42.874
I see what you're trying to do,
you know.

09:46.044 --> 09:47.546
Come on, this is almost done.

09:47.546 --> 09:50.382
Trust me, if you can't handle
your book on mushrooms

09:50.382 --> 09:51.633
or whatever that is...

09:53.343 --> 09:54.428
Was it mushrooms?

09:55.012 --> 09:56.346
Fungi.

09:56.346 --> 09:59.891
No, I hate the way
you barely need to read a book.

09:59.891 --> 10:02.269
And all the facts still
somehow get into your head.

10:02.269 --> 10:04.688
That's 'cause you've been
staring at it for hours.

10:04.688 --> 10:06.565
Yeah, I've been literally
staring at this page--

10:06.565 --> 10:09.026
I know, just leave it
and let's go to the pub!

10:13.739 --> 10:15.324
What was it like
growing up here?

10:15.324 --> 10:17.409
Growing up in London?
Yeah.

10:17.409 --> 10:19.328
Growing up in London
is just...

10:19.328 --> 10:21.955
there is always
low key something.

10:22.956 --> 10:24.499
I didn't actually
really clock it

10:24.499 --> 10:27.419
until the first time
I went to the countryside.

10:27.419 --> 10:31.048
And everything there
was, like, so quiet.

10:45.687 --> 10:47.272
I'm just going
to get another one,

10:47.272 --> 10:48.899
- is that all right?
- No problem.

11:20.472 --> 11:22.391
- Er, excuse me.
- Yeah, sorry?

11:22.391 --> 11:23.392
You don't have a lighter,
do you?

11:23.392 --> 11:25.560
I don't. Sorry.
I'm not a smoker myself.

11:25.560 --> 11:27.312
Right. That's very sensible.

11:27.312 --> 11:29.356
I like your hat you've got on,
by the way.

11:29.356 --> 11:31.316
- Well, thank you.
- Very interesting.

11:31.316 --> 11:32.484
Do I recognize you?

11:34.027 --> 11:35.904
- Possibly, are you from here?
- Yeah, yeah.

11:35.904 --> 11:37.155
Oh, I was thinking
from your accent

11:37.155 --> 11:38.615
you must be from somewhere else.

11:38.615 --> 11:40.492
No, er, my mum and dad
are English.

11:40.492 --> 11:42.786
- So I got a weird accent.
- That'll be it, that'll be it.

11:42.786 --> 11:44.371
Yeah, I've actually...
I've been away

11:44.371 --> 11:47.541
- for about ten years now. So...
- My God, long time.

11:47.541 --> 11:50.127
Yeah, I don't really come back
that often.

11:50.127 --> 11:51.461
So what are you doing now, then?

11:51.461 --> 11:53.547
I'm just going off to meet
a couple of friends.

11:53.547 --> 11:54.464
Ah, friends.

11:54.464 --> 11:56.258
Yeah.

11:56.258 --> 11:59.177
Yeah, I don't really know
anyone here anymore, so...

11:59.177 --> 12:01.471
I was a bit desperate to...

12:01.471 --> 12:03.765
see if there's anyone younger
hanging around.

12:03.765 --> 12:04.724
Oh, yes.

12:04.724 --> 12:06.935
Do you wanna have a cup of tea
before you go, maybe?

12:06.935 --> 12:09.271
No, I really can't.
I've got to catch up.

12:09.271 --> 12:11.148
- Another time, maybe.
- Right.

12:11.148 --> 12:13.608
Yeah. I'm staying
with my mum at the minute.

12:13.608 --> 12:15.819
But I usually live
down in London.

12:15.819 --> 12:18.822
I just came to help my dad
with the lambing, so...

12:18.822 --> 12:20.824
But I'm going
back down there soon, so...

12:21.825 --> 12:24.619
Mm. Er, could you
just give me your hand,

12:24.619 --> 12:25.912
so I can try this again?

12:25.912 --> 12:27.956
- Oh, yeah, no problem.
- All right, thanks.

12:32.127 --> 12:34.463
- The wind.
-  Yeah, it's not easy.

12:36.047 --> 12:37.924
- Got it!
- Yeah, all right.

12:37.924 --> 12:39.801
Okay, I gotta go on.
See you later.

12:39.801 --> 12:41.011
All right.

14:35.083 --> 14:38.086
<i>Sometimes you can feel
a vibration in Orkney.</i>

14:39.462 --> 14:40.755
<i>A low rumble.</i>

14:41.464 --> 14:42.632
<i>A tremor.</i>

14:43.592 --> 14:47.804
<i>It takes over the whole island
and every part of your body.</i>

14:49.097 --> 14:50.724
<i>But, of course...</i>

14:51.891 --> 14:53.560
<i>it could all just be
in your head.</i>

14:56.938 --> 14:58.398
<i>Some people say it's the sound</i>

14:58.398 --> 15:00.609
<i>of underwater
military experiments.</i>

15:05.905 --> 15:07.115
<i>Others say it's the waves</i>

15:07.115 --> 15:09.367
<i>caught in caves
deep below the land.</i>

15:13.204 --> 15:16.041
<i>But the one that brought me
nightmares when I was little</i>

15:16.625 --> 15:18.084
<i>is the oldest theory.</i>

15:19.169 --> 15:20.503
<i>A ginormous monster</i>

15:20.503 --> 15:22.589
<i>called the Mester Muckle
Stoorworm,</i>

15:22.589 --> 15:24.424
<i>who was so big</i>

15:24.424 --> 15:26.760
<i>his tail would wrap around
the whole world.</i>

15:27.510 --> 15:28.511
<i>And he was defeated</i>

15:28.511 --> 15:31.473
<i>by a young lad
called Assipattle.</i>

15:33.016 --> 15:35.852
<i>He killed the Stoorworm
with a burning peat.</i>

15:36.519 --> 15:39.189
<i>Fire burned inside its body.</i>

15:39.189 --> 15:40.649
<i>And it was in such pain</i>

15:40.649 --> 15:43.985
<i>that its neck reached
nine times to the moon and back.</i>

15:43.985 --> 15:45.820
<i>And then its teeth fell out</i>

15:46.404 --> 15:48.281
<i>and formed the Orkney islands.</i>

15:49.366 --> 15:51.660
<i>The liver
is still burning today.</i>

15:52.911 --> 15:55.038
<i>And we feel that as the tremors.</i>

16:06.091 --> 16:07.759
Oh, that was just lovely.

16:08.301 --> 16:09.678
Absolutely gorgeous.

16:09.678 --> 16:11.513
More mince,
if anyone wants another.

16:11.513 --> 16:13.056
- Couldn't have any more.
- No, thanks.

16:13.056 --> 16:15.141
Rona,
I notice you haven't eaten much.

16:15.141 --> 16:16.309
- You all right?
- Yeah, yeah.

16:16.309 --> 16:18.687
I'm just not hungry,
but it was lovely. Yeah.

16:19.396 --> 16:21.523
Excuse me.
Bless you.

16:21.523 --> 16:23.441
I'd just like to say thank you.

16:23.858 --> 16:26.236
Thank you, Father,
for this delicious food

16:26.236 --> 16:29.572
and for this wonderful company
at my table today.

16:30.240 --> 16:33.368
Of course we thank you,
Lord, for the food on our table,

16:33.368 --> 16:34.661
for the sun in the sky...

16:42.961 --> 16:44.504
<i>So are you up for long?</i>

16:44.504 --> 16:46.965
<i>No, I'm going back down
to London next week.</i>

16:46.965 --> 16:49.426
Just because, um,
there's a service for healing

16:49.426 --> 16:50.677
on a Thursday evening.

16:50.677 --> 16:52.429
You might find it interesting.

16:52.429 --> 16:54.264
Your husband used to go, right?

16:54.264 --> 16:56.182
Yeah, my Mark went,
like, last year.

16:56.182 --> 16:58.351
He was having
a bit of trouble with drinking

16:58.351 --> 16:59.978
and just needed
a bit of guidance

16:59.978 --> 17:01.980
and, you know,
just a bit of support and that.

17:01.980 --> 17:03.690
A bit of help, really,
you know, so...

17:03.690 --> 17:05.108
No, I'm doing fine, so...

17:05.108 --> 17:07.152
I mean, anyone can go.
It's not really like...

17:07.152 --> 17:08.611
Rona, your mum was saying

17:08.611 --> 17:10.613
that you're taking a break
from your study?

17:21.374 --> 17:23.042
Rona. Please don't.

17:23.042 --> 17:25.253
Don't what? Don't what? This?

17:26.421 --> 17:28.131
I'm sober. Do they know that?

17:28.923 --> 17:31.468
Because they seem to know
everything else, don't they?

17:33.720 --> 17:36.514
You've clearly told them
everything that's going on.

17:37.515 --> 17:38.767
Rona, I'm sorry.

17:41.936 --> 17:43.021
Come back inside?

17:43.021 --> 17:44.564
Give me a minute.

17:47.484 --> 17:49.903
Mm. Don't start reading
the Bible without me.

17:58.161 --> 18:00.622
<i>We want to see, we want to see</i>

18:01.372 --> 18:04.793
<i>We want to see Jesus lifted high</i>

18:04.793 --> 18:07.879
<i>We want to see, we want to see</i>

18:07.879 --> 18:09.047
<i>We want to see...</i>

18:22.644 --> 18:25.313
<i>Get a shift on, Daynin.
Come on.</i>

18:30.401 --> 18:31.903
Oh, fuck! Oh, fuck!

18:33.738 --> 18:35.949
-Daynin. Rona.
- Daynin.

18:35.949 --> 18:37.200
<i>Give me your hand!</i>

18:37.200 --> 18:38.368
Ah, give me your hand!

18:38.368 --> 18:40.995
Please, don't.
Two hands on the bicycle!

18:41.830 --> 18:45.875
<i>Happy birthday to you!</i>

18:47.460 --> 18:49.170
<i>Happy birthday...</i>

18:49.170 --> 18:50.380
Sorry!

18:50.380 --> 18:53.967
<i>Dear Gloria</i>

18:53.967 --> 18:57.637
<i>Happy birthday...</i>

19:58.990 --> 19:59.991
Hi.

20:01.326 --> 20:02.327
Hi.

20:31.522 --> 20:33.232
<i>Sometimes
when I hallucinate,</i>

20:34.067 --> 20:36.611
<i>I transpose
the island's boundaries</i>

20:36.611 --> 20:38.321
<i>onto a map of London.</i>

20:39.530 --> 20:41.908
<i>In Hackney, thousands of people</i>

20:41.908 --> 20:43.701
<i>live in the same area</i>

20:43.701 --> 20:46.621
<i>of the farm that was home
to just our family.</i>

20:47.747 --> 20:49.457
<i>150 acres.</i>

20:52.710 --> 20:56.297
<i>Screaming gulls are sirens,
the sea, traffic.</i>

20:57.090 --> 20:59.258
<i>Tower blocks are cliff faces.</i>

21:00.093 --> 21:02.512
<i>The warning lights
on top of tall buildings</i>

21:02.512 --> 21:03.805
<i>are lighthouses.</i>

21:05.014 --> 21:07.475
<i>The Tower of London
is Skara Brae.</i>

21:07.475 --> 21:10.770
<i>And the Millennium Dome
is the ancient Ring of Brodgar.</i>

21:49.434 --> 21:51.644
Rona, I just wanted
a quick catch up really,

21:51.644 --> 21:53.980
- just to see how you are.
-Yeah, good. Why?

21:53.980 --> 21:55.106
No, it's just that we had

21:55.106 --> 21:56.816
the lab meeting last week
and you weren't there.

21:56.816 --> 21:58.151
Everyone else was there.

21:58.151 --> 22:01.112
Well, yeah, I had, erm,
a dentist appointment that day.

22:01.112 --> 22:04.115
But also, I've just been
really busy with the project.

22:04.115 --> 22:05.450
You could've told me
about the dentist.

22:05.450 --> 22:06.993
I mean, some of the other guys
in the lab,

22:06.993 --> 22:08.745
they said that you sort of
distanced yourself a little bit.

22:08.745 --> 22:09.871
I did. Erm...

22:09.871 --> 22:11.581
That you're not going
to coffee with them

22:11.581 --> 22:13.291
- as much as you used to.
- Sorry. Erm...

22:17.462 --> 22:19.714
I mean, you had promised
to get a report to me

22:19.714 --> 22:21.299
last week as well.

23:17.814 --> 23:20.608
Have you ever felt like
you could control the weather?

23:21.609 --> 23:22.610
Really?

23:24.529 --> 23:25.905
Nah, that's not me.

23:26.781 --> 23:28.950
God, you're weird.

23:34.288 --> 23:35.414
You all right?

23:36.290 --> 23:37.333
Mm-hmm.

23:39.168 --> 23:40.169
Sure?

23:53.558 --> 23:54.934
I used to think

23:54.934 --> 23:58.437
my dad could control the wind,
when I was little.

24:02.942 --> 24:03.943
Dad!

24:07.905 --> 24:09.448
- Dad?
- Yeah.

24:09.448 --> 24:10.741
There you are.

24:11.325 --> 24:12.368
Hiya.

24:13.536 --> 24:14.996
- Hi.
- You all right?

24:14.996 --> 24:16.122
Yeah.

24:16.122 --> 24:18.457
I'm heading off soon,
so I wanted to say goodbye.

24:18.457 --> 24:19.750
- Are you?
- Yeah.

24:19.750 --> 24:21.502
- Already?
- Mm.

24:21.502 --> 24:23.296
Well, you want to see
a lump of something,

24:23.296 --> 24:25.548
- might be worth a fortune?
- What?

24:26.299 --> 24:28.050
"One test for ambergris
is to poke it

24:28.050 --> 24:30.386
with a hot needle
and a liquid should ooze out."

24:30.386 --> 24:31.804
Here we go.

24:36.309 --> 24:37.685
Look, look, look, look.

24:37.685 --> 24:39.395
That's liquid. Oh, my God!

24:39.395 --> 24:40.646
Wow.

24:41.439 --> 24:43.774
"Ambergris is a rare
and highly valuable substance

24:43.774 --> 24:45.735
produced in the stomach
of sperm whales,

24:45.735 --> 24:48.946
either vomited or excreted
and found floating on the seas.

24:48.946 --> 24:51.532
It has a bad smell."
Does it have a bad smell?

24:51.532 --> 24:52.950
Doesn't smell like anything.

24:52.950 --> 24:54.535
Still, that is liquid.

24:54.535 --> 24:58.456
- It says for one gram...
- Yes.

24:58.456 --> 25:00.333
...you can get $28.

25:00.333 --> 25:03.252
- What's that, 25 quid? 23 quid?
- Like 25 quid.

25:03.252 --> 25:05.546
Twenty-three, so that's,
that's... this is...

25:05.546 --> 25:07.924
This is ten pounds.
That's four and a half kilos,

25:07.924 --> 25:10.676
that's 4,500, that's... 25...

25:10.676 --> 25:12.803
That's over 100,000 pounds.

25:14.555 --> 25:16.432
That's over 100...

25:18.142 --> 25:18.976
Well done!

25:18.976 --> 25:20.353
That is one big tractor.

25:20.353 --> 25:22.313
- Seriously?
- My God.

25:22.897 --> 25:24.815
Oh, my.

25:25.524 --> 25:26.817
Will you send me updates
when you hear?

25:26.817 --> 25:28.653
- Well now, why don't you stay?
- No, I can't.

25:28.653 --> 25:30.238
Tell you what
I could do help with.

25:30.238 --> 25:31.989
A couple of the dikes
have come down

25:31.989 --> 25:34.116
on the outrun there,
and I could use some help

25:34.116 --> 25:35.409
building them back up again.

25:35.409 --> 25:37.370
