01:41:22.535 --> 01:41:24.662
- are we?
- Absolutely not.

01:41:24.662 --> 01:41:26.414
I should go back then.

01:41:26.414 --> 01:41:28.792
At least I can cook for him,
I can get him stuff in.

01:41:28.792 --> 01:41:30.585
Rona, please,
don't worry so much.

01:41:30.585 --> 01:41:31.753
-But I do worry.
- No.

01:41:31.753 --> 01:41:34.464
He's had to go through this
over and over again.

01:41:34.464 --> 01:41:36.841
You know,
you have to look after yourself.

01:41:36.841 --> 01:41:39.928
That's what I had to do,
you know.

01:41:43.640 --> 01:41:45.266
Was it really hard for you?

01:41:46.643 --> 01:41:48.520
Just having me, having the farm,

01:41:48.520 --> 01:41:51.272
he just wasn't... there.

01:41:53.107 --> 01:41:54.442
Mm, it was.

01:41:54.943 --> 01:41:55.944
It was.

01:41:56.736 --> 01:41:58.655
At times it was very difficult.

01:42:00.490 --> 01:42:02.033
He'd be away for months.

01:42:03.493 --> 01:42:06.913
And then even when
he wasn't away, I was...

01:42:08.248 --> 01:42:09.874
very lonely, sometimes.

01:42:11.960 --> 01:42:13.336
- Mm.
- Yeah.

01:42:15.129 --> 01:42:17.090
Then I found God, or rather...

01:42:18.007 --> 01:42:19.425
God found me.

01:42:22.512 --> 01:42:23.513
Mm.

01:42:47.620 --> 01:42:49.747
<i>All things come
from the ocean.</i>

01:42:49.747 --> 01:42:51.624
<i>And the ocean takes them back.</i>

01:42:52.417 --> 01:42:53.918
<i>And eventually, one day,</i>

01:42:53.918 --> 01:42:56.254
<i>they might come back again
to the land.</i>

01:43:02.302 --> 01:43:05.013
<i>After a gale is when
the best things are found.</i>

01:43:14.647 --> 01:43:17.066
<i>Parts of the Udal Law
from old Norse times</i>

01:43:17.066 --> 01:43:18.985
<i>still apply in Orkney.</i>

01:43:21.446 --> 01:43:24.115
<i>And if you find something
on the shore of your farmland,</i>

01:43:24.115 --> 01:43:26.242
<i>and its above
the low water mark,</i>

01:43:27.118 --> 01:43:28.119
<i>it's yours.</i>

01:44:00.443 --> 01:44:02.570
<i>There's a festival
that's about to happen here,</i>

01:44:02.570 --> 01:44:03.905
<i>it's called the Gyro Nights.</i>

01:44:03.905 --> 01:44:04.822
<i>Oh.</i>

01:44:04.822 --> 01:44:07.241
So all these artists
from all over the country,

01:44:07.241 --> 01:44:09.160
all over the world actually
are coming in.

01:44:09.160 --> 01:44:12.664
And we've been, like,
arranging the whole thing.

01:44:12.664 --> 01:44:14.248
And putting banners up.

01:44:14.248 --> 01:44:16.209
<i>- Oh, yeah?</i>
- Mm-hmm.

01:44:16.209 --> 01:44:18.544
<i>You're coming for my job.</i>

01:44:20.046 --> 01:44:23.132
<i>So, erm, no, but really,
how are you doing?</i>

01:44:23.132 --> 01:44:24.425
I'm fine.

01:44:24.425 --> 01:44:27.512
- I'm actually, yeah...
<i>- I mean, you look great, like...</i>

01:44:27.512 --> 01:44:31.307
I'm probably the best I've been
in a really long time.

01:44:32.809 --> 01:44:33.810
Promise.

01:45:04.257 --> 01:45:05.299
Gyro!

01:45:06.676 --> 01:45:07.760
Gyro!

01:45:08.970 --> 01:45:10.013
Gyro!

01:45:13.516 --> 01:45:15.435
I got it. Yeah, I got it.

01:45:49.385 --> 01:45:50.928
Do you want to sit down?

01:45:50.928 --> 01:45:52.513
Yeah, please.

01:45:54.849 --> 01:45:56.434
- It's a bit messy.
- That's okay.

01:45:56.434 --> 01:45:57.518
Here you go.

01:46:02.356 --> 01:46:03.399
So cold.

01:46:04.609 --> 01:46:06.069
Do you mind
if I take my socks off?

01:46:06.069 --> 01:46:07.820
No. That's what I'm gonna do.

01:46:07.820 --> 01:46:08.905
Soaking wet.

01:46:10.031 --> 01:46:11.199
Give me the socks.

01:46:11.199 --> 01:46:12.283
Thank you.

01:46:15.495 --> 01:46:17.747
- Ah, that's better.
- So much better.

01:46:17.747 --> 01:46:19.916
I loved that tonight,
it was fun.

01:46:20.374 --> 01:46:21.501
Such a nice evening.

01:46:21.501 --> 01:46:23.503
I actually had a dream
the other night

01:46:23.503 --> 01:46:26.255
- that all my hair was on fire.
- Okay.

01:46:26.255 --> 01:46:28.508
That sounds quite scary.

01:46:28.508 --> 01:46:30.968
Yeah. Kind of amazing, though.

01:46:31.719 --> 01:46:35.014
My hair was just flames
running around.

01:46:38.893 --> 01:46:41.145
So, you go back tomorrow?

01:46:41.145 --> 01:46:43.189
Yeah, getting the ferry
in the morning.

01:46:46.442 --> 01:46:47.443
Hmm.

01:46:54.867 --> 01:46:55.868
Hmm.

01:47:20.852 --> 01:47:22.854
<i>In grandiose moments,</i>

01:47:22.854 --> 01:47:26.524
<i>high on fresh air
and freedom on the hill,</i>

01:47:26.524 --> 01:47:28.776
<i>I study my personal geology.</i>

01:47:31.112 --> 01:47:32.989
<i>My body is a continent.</i>

01:47:35.449 --> 01:47:37.702
<i>I grind my teeth in my sleep</i>

01:47:37.702 --> 01:47:39.912
<i>like tectonic plates.</i>

01:47:41.414 --> 01:47:43.875
<i>And when I blink,
the sun flickers.</i>

01:47:45.710 --> 01:47:48.462
<i>My breath pushes the clouds
across the sky.</i>

01:47:48.462 --> 01:47:50.923
<i>And the waves roll
in to the shore</i>

01:47:50.923 --> 01:47:53.009
<i>in time with my beating heart.</i>

01:47:55.553 --> 01:47:58.222
<i>The island's headlands
rise above the sea</i>

01:47:58.222 --> 01:48:00.516
<i>like my limbs in the bathtub.</i>

01:48:01.893 --> 01:48:04.770
<i>My freckles
are famous landmarks.</i>

01:48:05.605 --> 01:48:08.149
<i>And my tears, rivers.</i>

01:48:10.860 --> 01:48:13.905
<i>Lightning strikes
every time I sneeze.</i>

01:48:15.281 --> 01:48:16.657
<i>And when I orgasm,</i>

01:48:17.450 --> 01:48:18.910
<i>there is an earthquake.</i>

01:51:58.295 --> 01:52:00.131
Mm?
